result.name: Yoshinoya

reviews.text: Good tasting food, but the hotpot takes forever. From the time we ordered the hotpot (per the receipt) to the time the water was boiling and ready to eat was more than 50 min. So don't get hotpot if you're starving. It did taste good though.

Although they have a limited set of options compared to their competitors like MX and Cafe de Coral, their food is quite homely. Their portions are not as large but actually quite right. It's one person one bowl. They do not accept cards but only cash or via octopus. Their service is decent and there is enough space to sit and eat in.

Relatively low cost, fast food Japanese food chain. The standard Beef Bowl is delicious and considering it's fast food, isn't as bad for you as other chains.

I recommend the Beef Bowl with a Soft Boiled Egg that you mix in with the rice and thin slices of beef.
Good value
nice food

reviews.text: 吉野家，愈黎愈差，牛肉少，飯乾淨淨一舊舊，早餐雞肉烏冬，雞扮一舊砌成三料，碗野只有咸味，兩粒星係唔想踩得太盡
他們說 火鍋要等一陣今天太多人了！ 但是我看見 到時六成人
態度極差,畀面色客人睇,經常睇錯單,畀錯野！
